BACKGROUND	O
OF	O
THE	O
INVENTION	O
1	O
.	O
Field	O
of	O
the	O
Invention	O
The	O
present	O
invention	O
relates	O
to	O
the	O
field	O
of	O
personnel	O
transport	O
apparatus	O
,	O
and	O
specifically	O
to	O
elevators	O
and	O
similar	O
devices	O
for	O
transporting	O
people	O
from	O
one	O
location	O
to	O
another	O
which	O
incorporate	O
various	O
information	O
technologies	O
.	O

2	O
.	O
Description	O
of	O
Related	O
Technology	O
Elevators	O
and	O
similar	O
personnel	O
transport	O
devices	O
(	O
such	O
as	O
moving	O
walkways	O
or	O
shuttles	O
)	O
are	O
important	O
aspects	O
of	O
modern	O
urban	O
life	O
.	O
Commonly	O
used	O
in	O
office	O
buildings	O
,	O
airports	O
,	O
shopping	O
malls	O
,	O
and	O
other	O
large	O
structures	O
,	O
these	O
devices	O
transport	O
large	O
numbers	O
of	O
people	O
and	O
equipment	O
between	O
two	O
locations	O
on	O
a	O
routine	O
basis	O
.	O
Elevators	O
in	O
particular	O
are	O
widely	O
used	O
throughout	O
the	O
world	O
.	O

Depending	O
on	O
loading	O
,	O
a	O
person	O
may	O
spend	O
up	O
to	O
several	O
minutes	O
on	O
an	O
elevator	O
during	O
travel	O
between	O
floors	O
.	O
Significant	O
amounts	O
of	O
time	O
may	O
also	O
be	O
spent	O
waiting	O
for	O
the	O
elevator	O
to	O
arrive	O
when	O
called	O
.	O
This	O
time	O
is	O
usually	O
“	O
dead	O
”	O
from	O
the	O
standpoint	O
that	O
very	O
little	O
can	O
be	O
accomplished	O
or	O
very	O
few	O
tasks	O
undertaken	O
during	O
these	O
few	O
minutes	O
.	O
However	O
,	O
often	O
times	O
an	O
individual	O
may	O
require	O
information	O
which	O
will	O
be	O
of	O
use	O
after	O
leaving	O
the	O
elevator	O
.	O
For	O
example	O
,	O
the	O
person	O
may	O
wish	O
to	O
obtain	O
travel	O
information	O
such	O
as	O
directions	O
to	O
the	O
nearest	O
airport	O
or	O
public	O
transportation	O
node	O
,	O
or	O
the	O
location	O
of	O
a	O
nearby	O
restaurant	O
.	O
Weather-related	O
information	O
or	O
traffic	O
reports	O
may	O
also	O
be	O
useful	O
.	O
A	O
plethora	O
of	O
different	O
types	O
of	O
information	O
,	O
including	O
financial	O
data	O
,	O
breaking	O
news	O
headlines	O
,	O
sports	O
scores	O
and	O
the	O
like	O
may	O
also	O
be	O
of	O
interest	O
to	O
one	O
waiting	O
for	O
or	O
riding	O
on	O
an	O
elevator	O
or	O
other	O
transport	O
device	O
.	O

An	O
associated	O
problem	O
relates	O
to	O
determining	O
the	O
location	O
of	O
a	O
person	O
,	O
firm	O
,	O
or	O
store	O
within	O
a	O
building	O
when	O
unfamiliar	O
.	O
Building	O
directories	O
are	O
often	O
posted	O
in	O
the	O
lobby	O
of	O
the	O
building	O
,	O
yet	O
these	O
require	O
the	O
user	O
to	O
manually	O
or	O
visually	O
locate	O
the	O
name	O
of	O
the	O
person	O
,	O
firm	O
,	O
or	O
store	O
which	O
they	O
are	O
looking	O
for	O
,	O
and	O
remember	O
the	O
location	O
information	O
associated	O
therewith	O
.	O
Additionally	O
,	O
such	O
directories	O
often	O
do	O
not	O
provide	O
precise	O
location	O
information	O
,	O
but	O
rather	O
merely	O
a	O
floor	O
number	O
and/or	O
suite	O
number	O
.	O
The	O
user	O
often	O
times	O
does	O
not	O
have	O
a	O
graphical	O
representation	O
of	O
the	O
desired	O
location	O
in	O
relation	O
to	O
the	O
elevators	O
,	O
thereby	O
resulting	O
in	O
additional	O
wasted	O
time	O
in	O
finding	O
the	O
location	O
once	O
off	O
of	O
the	O
elevator	O
.	O
Even	O
if	O
a	O
graphical	O
display	O
is	O
provided	O
,	O
it	O
often	O
requires	O
the	O
user	O
to	O
spatially	O
orient	O
themselves	O
to	O
determine	O
relative	O
location	O
.	O

Security	O
is	O
also	O
a	O
concern	O
when	O
riding	O
elevators	O
late	O
at	O
night	O
or	O
to	O
remote	O
locations	O
.	O
Many	O
elevator	O
systems	O
are	O
used	O
partly	O
or	O
entirely	O
within	O
parking	O
garages	O
,	O
which	O
often	O
may	O
be	O
sparsely	O
populated	O
at	O
off	O
hours	O
.	O
People	O
are	O
all	O
too	O
frequently	O
assaulted	O
or	O
robbed	O
when	O
departing	O
from	O
elevators	O
under	O
such	O
conditions	O
.	O
Unfortunately	O
,	O
existing	O
elevator	O
systems	O
do	O
not	O
have	O
the	O
facility	O
to	O
provide	O
the	O
occupant	O
(	O
s	O
)	O
with	O
the	O
ability	O
to	O
selectively	O
observe	O
the	O
area	O
immediately	O
surrounding	O
the	O
elevator	O
doors	O
on	O
one	O
or	O
more	O
destination	O
floors	O
,	O
or	O
otherwise	O
take	O
precautions	O
to	O
enhance	O
their	O
security	O
.	O

Another	O
problem	O
associated	O
with	O
existing	O
elevator	O
systems	O
relates	O
to	O
their	O
loading	O
capacity	O
.	O
Often	O
,	O
especially	O
at	O
peak	O
use	O
hours	O
such	O
as	O
during	O
the	O
noon	O
hour	O
,	O
the	O
call	O
buttons	O
for	O
several	O
different	O
floors	O
within	O
a	O
building	O
will	O
be	O
activated	O
,	O
and	O
elevator	O
cars	O
which	O
are	O
at	O
or	O
near	O
their	O
loading	O
capacity	O
will	O
respond	O
.	O
With	O
no	O
additional	O
room	O
available	O
in	O
the	O
elevator	O
,	O
the	O
person	O
depressing	O
the	O
call	O
button	O
on	O
a	O
given	O
floor	O
is	O
left	O
to	O
wait	O
for	O
the	O
elevator	O
doors	O
to	O
close	O
,	O
depress	O
the	O
call	O
button	O
again	O
,	O
and	O
wait	O
for	O
another	O
(	O
hopefully	O
partially	O
vacant	O
)	O
car	O
to	O
arrive	O
.	O
This	O
process	O
not	O
only	O
delays	O
the	O
person	O
waiting	O
for	O
the	O
car	O
,	O
but	O
also	O
those	O
on	O
the	O
elevator	O
car	O
(	O
s	O
)	O
,	O
and	O
those	O
waiting	O
on	O
other	O
floors	O
.	O

In	O
addition	O
to	O
the	O
foregoing	O
,	O
many	O
elevators	O
must	O
have	O
a	O
means	O
of	O
restricting	O
access	O
to	O
certain	O
floors	O
during	O
certain	O
time	O
periods	O
while	O
not	O
interfering	O
with	O
other	O
operations	O
.	O
These	O
elevators	O
generally	O
also	O
include	O
means	O
by	O
which	O
certain	O
users	O
may	O
gain	O
access	O
to	O
the	O
restricted	O
floors	O
,	O
such	O
as	O
a	O
magnetic	O
striped	O
card	O
which	O
is	O
inserted	O
into	O
a	O
card	O
reader	O
on	O
the	O
elevator	O
.	O
However	O
,	O
such	O
card	O
readers	O
are	O
prone	O
to	O
wear	O
and	O
having	O
to	O
re-swipe	O
the	O
card	O
several	O
times	O
in	O
order	O
to	O
obtain	O
access	O
.	O
Furthermore	O
,	O
as	O
the	O
card	O
wears	O
due	O
to	O
repeated	O
swiping	O
or	O
bending	O
(	O
such	O
as	O
when	O
left	O
in	O
the	O
pocket	O
of	O
the	O
individual	O
carrying	O
the	O
card	O
)	O
,	O
the	O
card	O
will	O
be	O
more	O
prone	O
to	O
failure	O
and	O
will	O
eventually	O
require	O
replacement	O
.	O
Also	O
,	O
such	O
cards	O
are	O
prone	O
to	O
unauthorized	O
use	O
.	O
Someone	O
stealing	O
or	O
finding	O
the	O
lost	O
card	O
can	O
simply	O
insert	O
it	O
into	O
the	O
card	O
reader	O
of	O
the	O
elevator	O
and	O
gain	O
access	O
to	O
the	O
restricted	O
floor	O
(	O
s	O
)	O
.	O
It	O
is	O
also	O
noted	O
that	O
since	O
access	O
is	O
restricted	O
to	O
certain	O
floors	O
typically	O
during	O
late-night	O
or	O
weekend	O
hours	O
,	O
HVAC	O
and	O
lighting	O
systems	O
are	O
typically	O
turned	O
off	O
or	O
dormant	O
in	O
order	O
to	O
conserve	O
energy	O
.	O
Hence	O
,	O
when	O
the	O
user	O
arrives	O
at	O
one	O
of	O
these	O
restricted	O
access	O
floors	O
,	O
several	O
minutes	O
are	O
typically	O
spent	O
turning	O
on	O
the	O
HVAC	O
,	O
lights	O
,	O
and	O
any	O
other	O
number	O
of	O
electrical	O
devices	O
.	O
Some	O
systems	O
require	O
the	O
user	O
to	O
insert	O
their	O
magnetic	O
strip	O
card	O
in	O
a	O
separate	O
reader	O
,	O
such	O
as	O
in	O
