associated	O
with	O
riding	O
an	O
elevator	O
car	O
,	O
especially	O
when	O
several	O
individuals	O
are	O
present	O
in	O
the	O
car	O
.	O
Due	O
in	O
part	O
to	O
minimal	O
space	O
within	O
the	O
car	O
and	O
nothing	O
to	O
occupy	O
the	O
occupants	O
attention	O
visually	O
,	O
there	O
is	O
a	O
natural	O
tendency	O
for	O
one	O
to	O
stare	O
up	O
,	O
down	O
,	O
or	O
forward	O
at	O
the	O
door	O
of	O
the	O
elevator	O
,	O
or	O
at	O
the	O
visual	O
floor	O
indicators	O
so	O
as	O
to	O
avoid	O
prolonged	O
eye	O
contact	O
with	O
the	O
other	O
occupants	O
.	O

Heretofore	O
,	O
many	O
of	O
the	O
technologies	O
necessary	O
to	O
address	O
the	O
aforementioned	O
issues	O
have	O
not	O
been	O
available	O
or	O
,	O
alternatively	O
,	O
have	O
been	O
cost	O
or	O
space	O
prohibitive	O
to	O
implement	O
.	O
However	O
,	O
recent	O
advances	O
in	O
data	O
networking	O
,	O
thin	O
or	O
flat	O
panel	O
display	O
technology	O
,	O
personal	O
electronics	O
,	O
and	O
speech	O
recognition	O
and	O
compression	O
algorithms	O
and	O
processing	O
have	O
enhanced	O
the	O
viability	O
of	O
such	O
features	O
from	O
both	O
technological	O
and	O
commercial	O
perspectives	O
.	O

Based	O
on	O
the	O
foregoing	O
,	O
there	O
is	O
a	O
need	O
for	O
an	O
improved	O
elevator	O
system	O
and	O
method	O
of	O
operation	O
which	O
will	O
reduce	O
the	O
time	O
spent	O
waiting	O
for	O
and	O
travelling	O
on	O
the	O
elevator	O
car	O
,	O
reduce	O
the	O
frustration	O
associated	O
with	O
repeated	O
stops	O
at	O
different	O
floors	O
,	O
and	O
allow	O
the	O
occupants	O
of	O
the	O
elevator	O
(	O
as	O
well	O
as	O
those	O
waiting	O
for	O
the	O
car	O
)	O
to	O
use	O
their	O
time	O
more	O
efficiently	O
and	O
obtain	O
needed	O
information	O
.	O
Additionally	O
,	O
such	O
an	O
elevator	O
system	O
would	O
enhance	O
the	O
security	O
of	O
the	O
occupants	O
upon	O
egress	O
,	O
and	O
allow	O
for	O
automatic	O
recognition	O
of	O
an	O
individual	O
in	O
order	O
to	O
provide	O
access	O
to	O
certain	O
restricted	O
locations	O
and	O
initiation	O
of	O
certain	O
functions	O
such	O
as	O
lighting	O
and	O
HVAC	O
.	O

SUMMARY	O
OF	O
THE	O
INVENTION	O
The	O
present	O
invention	O
satisfies	O
the	O
aforementioned	O
needs	O
by	O
providing	O
an	O
improved	O
elevator	O
information	O
and	O
control	O
system	O
and	O
method	O
of	O
operating	O
the	O
same	O
In	O
a	O
first	O
aspect	O
,	O
the	O
present	O
invention	O
provides	O
an	O
improved	O
elevator	O
information	O
and	O
control	O
system	O
which	O
enables	O
an	O
user	O
to	O
rapidly	O
locate	O
a	O
desired	O
firm	O
or	O
individual	O
.	O
In	O
a	O
first	O
embodiment	O
,	O
the	O
system	O
includes	O
an	O
interactive	O
building	O
directory	O
having	O
a	O
speech	O
recognition	O
system	O
and	O
other	O
input	O
device	O
such	O
as	O
a	O
touch	O
pad	O
.	O
The	O
user	O
utilizes	O
the	O
input	O
device	O
to	O
activate	O
the	O
system	O
,	O
and	O
then	O
speaks	O
the	O
name	O
of	O
the	O
firm	O
or	O
individual	O
whose	O
location	O
is	O
desired	O
.	O
A	O
speech	O
generation	O
algorithm	O
and	O
processor	O
generates	O
speech	O
(	O
and/or	O
a	O
graphical	O
representation	O
via	O
a	O
minimum	O
profile	O
flat	O
panel	O
display	O
)	O
based	O
on	O
data	O
retrieved	O
from	O
a	O
database	O
per	O
the	O
user	O
's	O
request	O
.	O
The	O
user	O
is	O
also	O
prompted	O
to	O
determine	O
if	O
they	O
desire	O
to	O
select	O
the	O
floor	O
of	O
the	O
firm	O
or	O
individual	O
that	O
they	O
were	O
trying	O
to	O
locate	O
.	O
The	O
user	O
then	O
may	O
use	O
the	O
speech	O
recognition	O
system	O
,	O
or	O
alternatively	O
the	O
aforementioned	O
input	O
device	O
,	O
to	O
respond	O
.	O
The	O
database	O
also	O
maintains	O
data	O
on	O
other	O
nearby	O
buildings	O
in	O
case	O
the	O
user	O
is	O
at	O
the	O
wrong	O
location	O
.	O

In	O
a	O
second	O
aspect	O
of	O
the	O
invention	O
,	O
the	O
information	O
and	O
control	O
system	O
further	O
includes	O
a	O
network	O
interface	O
that	O
is	O
coupled	O
to	O
the	O
aforementioned	O
input	O
and	O
display	O
devices	O
.	O
In	O
one	O
embodiment	O
,	O
the	O
network	O
(	O
e.g.	O
,	O
Internet	O
)	O
interface	O
is	O
configured	O
to	O
provide	O
rapid	O
access	O
to	O
a	O
variety	O
of	O
web	O
sites	O
or	O
URLs	O
of	O
interest	O
,	O
such	O
as	O
those	O
providing	O
local	O
weather	O
,	O
directions	O
from	O
the	O
elevator	O
to	O
local	O
points	O
of	O
interest	O
,	O
stock	O
market	O
quotations	O
,	O
breaking	O
news	O
headlines	O
,	O
etc	O
.	O
Preset	O
functions	O
are	O
provided	O
which	O
enable	O
the	O
user	O
to	O
access	O
,	O
download	O
,	O
and	O
display	O
the	O
desired	O
information	O
with	O
a	O
single	O
actuation	O
of	O
the	O
input	O
device	O
.	O
A	O
plurality	O
of	O
different	O
input/display	O
devices	O
are	O
disposed	O
within	O
the	O
smart	O
elevator	O
to	O
allow	O
multiple	O
occupants	O
to	O
obtain	O
information	O
simultaneously	O
.	O

In	O
a	O
third	O
aspect	O
of	O
the	O
invention	O
,	O
the	O
smart	O
elevator	O
includes	O
one	O
or	O
more	O
data	O
terminals	O
which	O
are	O
compatible	O
with	O
personal	O
electronic	O
devices	O
(	O
PEDs	O
)	O
so	O
as	O
to	O
allow	O
an	O
occupant	O
of	O
the	O
elevator	O
to	O
download	O
a	O
predetermined	O
or	O
adaptively	O
determined	O
“	O
package	O
”	O
of	O
data	O
for	O
later	O
retrieval	O
or	O
use	O
.	O
Such	O
data	O
may	O
include	O
news	O
,	O
weather	O
,	O
financial	O
data	O
,	O
listings	O
of	O
building	O
tenants	O
,	O
firm	O
resumes	O
,	O
parking	O
rates	O
,	O
hours	O
of	O
operation	O
,	O
and	O
the	O
like	O
.	O
In	O
one	O
embodiment	O
,	O
the	O
download	O
of	O
data	O
is	O
initiated	O
automatically	O
upon	O
the	O
insertion	O
of	O
the	O
PED	O
into	O
the	O
data	O
terminal	O
,	O
thereby	O
reducing	O
the	O
time	O
necessary	O
to	O
download	O
to	O
a	O
minimum	O
.	O

In	O
a	O
fourth	O
aspect	O
of	O
the	O
invention	O
,	O
the	O
information	O
and	O
control	O
system	O
includes	O
a	O
sensor	O
array	O
and	O
logic	O
which	O
detects	O
the	O
loading	O
of	O
the	O
elevator	O
car	O
and	O
selectively	O
bypasses	O
floors	O
when	O
the	O
car	O
's	O
capacity	O
is	O
met	O
,	O
unless	O
the	O
floor	O
is	O
selected	O
by	O
one	O
of	O
the	O
occupants	O
of	O
the	O
car	O
.	O
In	O
one	O
embodiment	O
,	O
the	O
flooring	O
of	O
the	O
elevator	O
car	O
is	O
equipped	O
with	O
piezoelectric	O
sensors	O
that	O
generate	O
signals	O
based	O
on	O
the	O
pressure	O
applied	O
to	O
them	O
.	O
This	O
pressure	O
is	O
correlated	O
to	O
the	O
weight	O
and	O
location	O
of	O
the	O
occupants	O
in	O
the	O
car	O
,	O
and	O
with	O
the	O
number	O
of	O
different	O
floors	O
selected	O
,	O
to	O
derive	O
an	O
estimate	O
of	O
the	O
occupancy	O
.	O
When	O
the	O
capacity	O
of	O
the	O
elevator	O
is	O
reached	O
as	O
determined	O
by	O
this	O
estimate	O
,	O
any	O
subsequent	O
call	O
signals	O
received	O
by	O
the	O
system	O
are	O
routed	O
to	O
another	O
available	O
car	O
.	O

In	O
a	O
fifth	O
aspect	O
of	O
the	O
invention	O
,	O
the	O
aforementioned	O
display	O
device	O
within	O
the	O
car	O
may	O
be	O
configured	O
to	O
provide	O
a	O
video	O
display	O
of	O
the	O
area	O
immediately	O
surrounding	O
access	O
to	O
the	O
elevator	O
on	O
certain	O
floors	O
,	O
such	O
as	O
parking	O
garages	O
.	O
The	O
user	O
can	O
over-ride	O
the	O
car	O
stopping	O
at	O
that	O
floor	O
if	O
desired	O
,	O
contact	O
security	O
,	O
and/or	O
initiate	O
